{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8dc1964-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s702"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"702"},"text":"§ 702.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Uniform of armed forces and Public Health Service","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Whoever, in any place within the jurisdiction of the United States or in the Canal Zone, without authority, wears the uniform or a distinctive part thereof or anything similar to a distinctive part of the uniform of any of the armed forces of the United States, Public Health Service or any auxiliary of such, shall be fined under this title or imprisoned not more than six months, or both.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8dc1965-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 645","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/732"},"text":"62 Stat. 732","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-05-24/ch139/s15/a"},"text":"May 24, 1949, ch. 139, § 15(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/91"},"text":"63 Stat. 91","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322/tXXXIII/s330016/1/E"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322, title XXXIII, § 330016(1)(E)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2146"},"text":"108 Stat. 2146","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8dc1966-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb8dc1967-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb8dc1968-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"1948 ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1393"},"text":"section 1393 of title 10","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., Army and Air Force, and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s228"},"text":"section 228 of title 42","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., 1940 ed., The Public Health and Welfare ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1916-06-03/ch134/s125"},"text":"June 3, 1916, ch. 134, § 125","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/39/216"},"text":"39 Stat. 216","children":[],"tail":" (2d paragraph); "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373/s510"},"text":"July 1, 1944, ch. 373, § 510","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/58/711"},"text":"58 Stat. 711","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Auxiliary of such” was inserted to extend protection to the uniforms of any auxiliary corps that may be established.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Fine of “$250” was substituted for “$300” as being more consonant with the penalties provided for similar offenses in this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Minor changes of phraseology also were made.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb8dc1969-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"1949 ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section [section 15] inserts “armed forces” in the catch line and text of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s702"},"text":"section 702 of title 18","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C., and thereby includes the Air Force which was formerly part of the Army. (See note to sec. 5 [of 1949 Act, set out in Legislative History note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s244"},"text":"section 244 of title 18","children":[],"tail":"]). Also, it incorporates in such section the provisions of act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-04-15"},"text":"April 15, 1948","children":[],"tail":" (ch. 188, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/172"},"text":"62 Stat. 172","children":[],"tail":"), which relates to this section as well as to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1393"},"text":"section 1393 of title 10","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C. (one of the sources of such sec. 701), as it existed at the time of the enactment of the revision of title 18 and which was not incorporated in title 18 when the revision was enacted. In this connection specific reference to the Canal Zone, Guam, American Samoa, and the Virgin Islands, as contained in such act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-04-15"},"text":"April 15, 1948","children":[],"tail":", were omitted as covered by the phrase, “in any place within the jurisdiction of the United States,” as used in this amendment of such "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s702"},"text":"section 702 of title 18","children":[],"tail":", U.S.C."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8dc196a-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb8dc196b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For definition of Canal Zone, referred to in text, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s3602/b"},"text":"section 3602(b) of Title 22","children":[],"tail":", Foreign Relations and Intercourse."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb8dc196c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322","children":[],"tail":" substituted “fined under this title” for “fined not more than $250”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1949—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1949","children":[],"tail":", inserted “armed forces” in lieu of enumerating specific branches in section catchline and text, and inserted “in any place within the jurisdiction of the United States or in the Canal Zone”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb8dc196d-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"idb8dc196e-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare redesignated Secretary of Health and Human Services by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/88/tV/s509/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–88, title V, § 509(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1979","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/93/695"},"text":"93 Stat. 695","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s3508/b"},"text":"section 3508(b) of Title 20","children":[],"tail":", Education."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idb8dc196f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"idb8dc1970-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions of Public Health Service, Surgeon General of Public Health Service, and all other officers and employees of Public Health Service, and functions of all agencies of or in Public Health Service transferred to Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare by Reorg. Plan No. 3 of 1966, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1966","children":[],"tail":", 31 F.R. 8855, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/1610"},"text":"80 Stat. 1610","children":[],"tail":", set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
